00:26:52.820 --> 00:26:55.010
And another one is
the asteroid modeling.

00:26:55.010 --> 00:26:57.770
So the dynamics that
we talked about with

00:26:57.770 --> 00:26:59.930
the early solar system
and what happened to it

00:26:59.930 --> 00:27:03.230
when you had all this
bombardment in the early days.

00:27:03.230 --> 00:27:06.300
When you couple that
to geochemical studies

00:27:06.300 --> 00:27:09.740
of the rocks that
people have found,

00:27:09.740 --> 00:27:13.780
either from meteorite samples
that have come off planet

00:27:13.780 --> 00:27:17.340
from someplace else, or the
lunar samples that came back

00:27:17.340 --> 00:27:20.530
from the Moon, you couple that
together with the dynamics,

00:27:20.530 --> 00:27:24.090
and you can learn an awful
lot about what happened when.

00:27:24.090 --> 00:27:27.490
And what we call the
late heavy bombardment

00:27:27.490 --> 00:27:31.870
period that affected both
the Earth and the Moon system

00:27:31.870 --> 00:27:33.560
is one of those times
that we'd really

00:27:33.560 --> 00:27:34.970
like to understand better.

00:27:34.970 --> 00:27:41.500
Because it looks very, very
likely that the moon formed out

00:27:41.500 --> 00:27:45.120
of a giant Mars-- not
giant, but a Mars-sized body

00:27:45.120 --> 00:27:46.590
hitting the Earth.

00:27:46.590 --> 00:27:48.920
And when it hit the
Earth, it knocked off

00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:50.510
a great deal of material.

00:27:50.510 --> 00:27:52.920
And out of that formed the Moon.

00:27:52.920 --> 00:27:55.910
But what didn't make
sense for a long time

00:27:55.910 --> 00:27:58.370
were the isotopic
studies that we

00:27:58.370 --> 00:28:01.360
had in the chemical composition
between the Moon and the Earth.

00:28:01.360 --> 00:28:03.950
Those are now coming
into much clearer focus

00:28:03.950 --> 00:28:08.970
in terms of how hot the Earth
was, how wet the Earth was,

00:28:08.970 --> 00:28:11.560
how big that body was, what
kind of angle that body had

00:28:11.560 --> 00:28:14.290
to hit the Earth at in
order to make what we end up

00:28:14.290 --> 00:28:15.720
seeing on the Moon.

00:28:15.720 --> 00:28:21.010
So it's just amazing that
dynamicists and geologists

00:28:21.010 --> 00:28:24.680
